[ ] graphd owns portable query families and output formats $Establish graphd as the direct public read/query/export tool. Standard .sparql files opt into index, tree, or graph consumer contracts by family directory; graphd validates and serializes them, while raw/named SPARQL stays unrestricted. The clearhead CLI remains a mutation and workspace-lifecycle convenience and should not forward, decode, or implement graph queries. Neovim and other clients call graphd directly for reads and clearhead for identity-addressed writes. Index output is proven; complete the direct-client cutover before implementing tree/work-map and graph/dependencies showcases.$ !2 #019f76ca-f3b1-7613-a0de-74f453f8576c
    >[ ] move clearhead.nvim query reads directly to graphd $Add explicit graphd binary discovery/configuration to clearhead.nvim and invoke graphd's public index interface directly. Keep clearhead only for mutation verbs and clearhead-lsp for document intelligence. Prove the existing read -> act-by-id -> re-read living loop with all three binaries independently addressable.$ #019f8b8a-723c-7350-b4a7-ef84bf6cb02c
    >[ ] retire the CLI query forwarding facade $After editor and documented consumers call graphd directly, remove clearhead query subcommands, graph_backend query forwarding, duplicated query format arguments, and facade tests/docs. Preserve only core-backed mutation/workspace commands in clearhead; graphd remains independently installable and owns query stdout, stderr, formats, and exit semantics.$ <019f8b8a-723c-7350-b4a7-ef84bf6cb02c #019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce
    >[ ] implement the tree query family with work-map $Add queries/tree discovery and execution around complete standard SELECT files. Use work-map.sparql as the proving query over charter, subcharter, action, and child-action hierarchy; validate canonical id plus parent semantics, emit nested JSON for machines and an indented terminal tree, and run the same .sparql unchanged in an external SPARQL tool.$ <019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce #019f8b8a-b7ef-7731-b870-8719fd562c33
    >[ ] implement the graph query family with dependencies $Add queries/graph discovery and standard CONSTRUCT execution. Use dependencies.sparql as the proving query over action identity, labels, states, charter membership, and predecessor edges; emit JSON-LD plus an explicit standard RDF format and a terminal summary, and prove the .sparql/result round-trip through external RDF tooling.$ <019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce #019f8b8a-b7fc-7e03-a507-2e47b88f4740
